canonical:
  title: 南遷過漢江
  author: 曺偉
  language: lzh
  text: 眊矂歸來不見天終南咫尺望雲烟三年塞下孤臣淚今日江頭倍黯然
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 南遷過漢江
  author: 曺偉
  language: lzh
  text: 眊矂歸來不見天。終南咫尺望雲烟。三年塞下孤臣淚。今日江頭倍黯然。
korean:
  title: 남천 과 한강
  author: 조위
  language: kor
  text: |-
    시름 속에 돌아오니 하늘도 아니 보이더니
    종남산 지척에서 내와 구름 바라보네
    세해 동안 저 변새에 외론 신하 그 눈물이
    오늘 이 강 위에선 더욱 아득하여라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0120&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Crossing the Han River on the Southern Migration
  author: Cao Wei
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Returning through sorrow, I cannot even see the sky.
    At the edge of Mount Zhongnan, I gaze upon mist and clouds.
    Three years of tears shed by a lonely minister at that distant frontier—
    Today by this river's edge, my heart grows only darker still.
  footnotes:
    - 'Mount Zhongnan (終南): a sacred mountain south of Chang''an, symbolizing the poet''s former place of service and the distance from home'
    - The "lonely minister" refers to the poet's exile or displacement, a common theme in classical Chinese poetry expressing separation from one's ruler and homeland
